Feeding an obese child: don't eat breakfast and take the tank for dinner
More than one third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 have overweight problems, 9% of schoolchildren will weigh above average and 5% are obese.
As current research shows, obese children come from families who have a unhealthy lifestyle.
This shows again how important is the environment in which the human being and the models around it evolve.
On the tables of obese children, for example, there is 50% more carcuterie than in normal weight families.
19% of the obese had dinner fries according to the survey carried out with awareness-raising action "Obey isn't a chance"
In small families sport is also not a habit, which is now the case of most schoolchildren today - only 15% replied that at least once a week parents found time for active movement.
Survey of 900 children
The survey took place during the last school year and attended 900 primary school students in Czechia.
It was the second edition of "Obeyance is not a chance", supported by General Health Insurance and Unilever.
Since the beginning, more than 12000 students from sixth to third have enrolled in this project.
One of the determining factors that causes a dramatic increase in the number of overweight or obese children is the absence of a proper diet and not enough physical exercise.
"Only half of the children questioned indicate, for example, eating 5 times a day breakfast-in case - lunch-eating- dinner, which is a basic principle of good food," says one of the results of the survey.
Without breakfast and dinner charcuerie
Specialists draw attention to the fact that to have healthy development you need some basic details such as a family breakfast at the same time.
In Czechia, only 23% of students' families eat at the same time.
In most families each takes his breakfast alone.
And the worst thing that has been raised is that one tenth of the population don't have breakfast at all.
Yet breakfast is the basis of good daily food.
The questionnaire showed that in obese children's families, unhealthy fries are more often consumed.
Almost every student - not to mention the weight - drinks sugar every day (70%).
More than 40% of the children asked make sport regularly, but for parents it's only half, 15%.
Prepare your food.
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to prepare their own food on the basis of opportunities offered according to their own taste and personal opinion.
"The preferences of Czech children between 12 and 15 years of age are far from ideal in terms of healthy diet."
Among their favorite dishes are many cakes, meats and sugars.
"The most alarming is in particular a great preference for sweet lemonades," is indicated in the results of the survey.
For lunch are the pasta that took the first place just in front of the white meat.
Children did not want to be fertilized at all, and the preference for fish and vegetable meals was very low.
Head of Health
The survey also showed that children are prepared to change their habits from the moment they receive the ad hoc information.
"During a review of a group of participants in the survey who had completed the questionnaire after the awareness session "Obviousness is not a coincidence", a determined desire to go to a healthy diet was observed," the results of the survey.
The most significant was for example in relation to sweet lemonades because children began to give preference to drinking water.
The children most often put white meat and fish on the questionnaire as a main dish and would reduce sweet dishes and "knedliky" (Czech specialty of breadmeal or potatoes flour).
