The result is well because this element is not likely to interfere and, in the context described above, is placed in the elements that please the game.
The driving model is in the tradition of previous games.
Which means that at present there is nothing extraordinary, but it cannot be said to be negative.
With regard to realistic simulation, you will have to go elsewhere.
But although we can find the driving model better in concordance, it works very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything's okay.
Problems begin to appear after a certain period of time.
With the difference of the driving model, the collision model is not yet in place.
We do not expect this game a complicated deformation and collisions, but when you don't have, in a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, it is not completely good.
During tight overruns you touch each other sometimes slightly but otherwise your car goes into crazy volts.
Or you'll find yourself in crumbs.
Thanks to the restart system this is not really a problem but it really bothers you.
The reboot is done so that when you have broken the figure or you have gone out into the decor the game brings you back to the last point on the itinerary.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used the 5 restarts you have to restart the game from the beginning.
So it's more a tool, in case something doesn't go the way it should be, than something you can really count on.
Sometimes restarts don't help and you need to find the solution by remembering the piece of route in question.
The big part of this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
