Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large American cylinders for right highways and super exotic sports cars on very technical roads, for example on laccia roads in the mountains.
And the way of challenges, which are racing in particular places you know about adventure, goes very well with the main regime of history.
You receive not only medals but also points of experience that add to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest driver level, different objects begin to unlock:
It connects online with the Autolog function that compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult to understand is the situation of the last race of adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (like it) where you drive in the dark on the tracks (like it).
Your speed indicator tells you between 150 and 200 km/h (a priori) and behind you comes a metro line that sends you the car directly to the scrap metal.
In writing we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone actually thought about creating this game or whether the authors really take us for fools.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally pleasant and in some cases really great.
What's bothering is that in more extreme situations, imaging does not keep level and in some cases tragically.
This concerns especially accidents with a large number of participants when a fluid imaging is no longer useful for you.
The sound part is good and the track is at the choice.
In order to please the greatest number and especially the young audience, a new sound track was created in the style "I mix everything", but one can expect that no one will buy the game for music.
General Impression of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore really confused.
If the game did not have these stupid mistakes we could safely say that it is the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game gives the impression that it is not finished.
The fun is really good but prepare yourself for the mistakes to tap into your eyes with the strength of an aerodrome reflector.
The Velvet Students in concert with the Choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivals that link the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs of high schools and secondary classes.
The festival's nail consists of two concerts organized on November 17.
Charles University has an important part in this festival.
"Among the choirs there is the Choeur of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the festival committee sits the rector Vaclav Hampl", says the head of the team organizing Jakub Calou.
The festival's nail is the concert of the Choeur des lycées et classes, which takes place with free entrance on November 17, starting at 2 p.m. on the space in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program includes the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening the concert "Students of Velvets" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of the upper schools and that of Charles University occur.
The aim of the Festa Academy is not only to celebrate with dignity the International Student Day and to recall the 22nd anniversary of the Velver Revolution, but also to present to the public a choir music of the highest level and develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Union of Czech Treasures in cooperation with high school Jan Kepler.
All the action is placed under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, mystical meetings, student encounters and other activities.
Interested people will find all information on the festival's web pages www.festaacademica.cz.
