History of a trade mark:
Innovator IBM begins the second century of its existence
If someone were to look for the word that expresses the IBM strategy as close as possible, the closest one would be "long term".
For a large audience IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, it is a firm felt as very current and yet since its creation it has been one hundred years.
The basis of this long-term strategy was laid by the first head of the firm, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He has left this slogan that a large number of global problems can be solved so little that people are willing to think.
His slogan "PENSE'!" became the footprint around which the life of a giant future will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began to edit in 1935).
It was the basis of the company's culture carefully developed by Watson.
For us IBM means a long-term thought of continuous movements towards the future.
IBM survived a hundred years thanks to the fact that it remains faithful to its core values and yet it was not afraid to change all others around it.
This allowed us in our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will reach even more," the current director of the company Samuel J. Palmisano announced for the anniversary.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the 1930s, began to take care of his employees such as Bata in the Czech Republic - IBM people were the only first American employees to have paid holidays, insurance paid by the employer plus an elegant employee uniform and a well-developed system of rewards for inventors and commercials.
Similarly IBM has a well-developed customer relationship system.
The society was at the beginning brilliant in the discovery of talent- as one of the first companies to have abolished all forms of discrimination and could thus have the choice.
The current plan is entirely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy as it will be a woman- Virginia Rometty - who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
It has been at IBM for 30 years and is currently in the position of Chief of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
In recent years IBM has done what is called jamy, brain-storming online from which many future strategies and innovations have emerged.
It is not surprising that there are many ideas - in the firm there are nearly 500,000 people working.
An institution with a good name
