This is an excerpt from the conversation, whose full transcript is found in La Nación on the Internet.
For its Costa Rican supporters, the fact that Pearl Jam will happen in Costa Rica is a dream come true. Are you aware of what your fans live?
Going to Costa Rica is a dream that has become a reality for us too.
This is our second time in South and Central America and has so far been great.
I spent only once in Costa Rica; it's such a beautiful country and I think we can spend a few days there.
We are therefore thrilled to carry our music there.
I ask you, because there is some kind of devotion to the group, fans live intensely in the days before.
What is your message for your most ardent followers?
Thank you for staying with us all these years.
It took 21 years for us to arrive in Costa Rica; thank you for waiting so long and we are sorry that so long had to pass up to this concert.
Some people already say that his concert is the biggest show of the year.
Does this add a little pressure to your visit?
Some of the biggest shows we've been offering over the last 21 years have taken place in the last two weeks.
